entry.tran: 时间表;时间安排;日程表
entry.def: A timetable is a plan of the times when particular events are to take place.

example.tran: 时间表制定得过于乐观。

example.ex: Don't you realize we're working to a timetable? We have to have results...
example.tran: 难道你没意识到我们是有一个时间表的吗？我们必须出成果。

entry.def: In a school or college, a timetable is a list that shows the times in the week at which particular subjects are taught. You can also refer to the range of subjects that a student learns or the classes that a teacher teaches as their timetable .

example.ex: Options are offered subject to staff availability and the constraints of the timetable...
example.tran: 课程选择视教师的时间与课程表的限制而定。

example.ex: Members of the union will continue to teach their full timetables.
example.tran: 协会成员将继续教授所有课程。

entry.def: A timetable is a list of the times when trains, boats, buses, or aeroplanes are supposed to arrive at or leave from a particular place.

example.ex: For a local bus timetable, contact Dyfed County Council.
example.tran: 若要当地公共汽车时刻表，请与达费德郡政务委员会联系。

entry.def: If something is timetabled, it is scheduled to happen or do something at a particular time.

example.ex: On both days, three very different trains will be timetabled...
example.tran: 这两天都将安排发出 3 列时刻不同的火车。

example.ex: Opie is timetabled to work a four-day week.
example.tran: 奥佩被安排每周工作 4 天。
